---
title: "Executive dysfunction relates to salience network desegregation in behavioural variant frontotemporal dementia"
collection: publications
category: manuscripts
excerpt: 'This study demonstrates associations between executive dysfunction and salience network de-differentiation in patients with bvFTD, suggesting that reduced neural capacity for specialized processing may contribute to executive dysfunction.'
date: 2025-07-24
venue: 'Neuroimage Clin'
paperurl: 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40716388/'
citation: 'Matyi MA, Radhakrishnan H, Olm CA, Phillips JS, Cook PA, Rhodes E, Gee JC, Irwin DJ, McMillan CT, Massimo L. (2025). &quot;Executive dysfunction relates to salience network desegregation in behavioural variant frontotemporal dementia.&quot; <i>Neuroimage Clin</i>. 48:103853.'
